-- PERMANENT negative control (PLAN_ELABORATOR_ERGONOMICS.md step E0).
--
-- `-1` with NOTHING to supply a carrier must stay rejected. E2 makes unary `-`
-- honor an expected carrier when one exists; it must not invent one when none
-- does.
--
-- Note the message here is currently identical to the PENDING probe in
-- carrier_pending_unary_numeral.math. That is expected: the difference is not
-- the message but the context — there an Integer carrier is available and is
-- being missed, here there is none. After E2 the pending file is deleted and
-- this one still fails.
--
-- An ordinary unseeded Natural expression such as `1 + 2` is of course legal
-- and is NOT what this control forbids.
module ErrorTest.unseeded_negative_numeral

import Natural.basics
import Natural.arithmetic

definition ErrorTest.control : Proposition := -1 = -1
